ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I would recommend the class.Interesting material. Great professor.
As an introduction to aquatic chemistry, I feel that the class could be useful to someone with that interest or whose research depends on it.

This course provides a useful overview of the chemical processes at play in natural aquatic systems. An understanding of many of these topics is important for understanding of many topics in environmental engineering. The class itself seemed to focus a bit too much on the arithmetic and calculations required to address these problems, but I would still recommend it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I have a deeper understanding of the subject
The class helped me become more comfortable with redox and acid/base chemistry, which may be helpful.
This course fit well with Professor Elimelech's course and helped illuminate the chemistry at play in some of the typical physical and chemical processes in environmental engineering.
